## <a id="reqs"></a>Requirements

Prisma Cloud for VMware Tanzu TAS has the following requirements:

* You have a Prisma Cloud license.
* For Prisma Cloud Compute Edition, you have installed Prisma Cloud Console.
Prisma Cloud Console is delivered as a container image.
You can run it on Pivotal Container Service (PKS) or a stand-alone virtual machine.
For stand-alone virtual machines, use the Onebox install target, which lets you quickly install Prisma Cloud components onto any Linux box with Docker Engine.
* For Prisma Cloud Enterprise Edition, Palo Alto Networks hosts the Console for you, so there are no prerequisites to install.


